questions.question: You read in a data dictionary in which missing values for a Precipitation (mm) attribute were represented by the value -99. Which of the following ways of conceptualizing "nothing" is the dataset using?
options: An attribute has a particular state that indicates nothingness (null)
An attribute has a particular value that indicates nothingness
An attribute exists but has no value (empty)

questions.question: A value of <missing> in the Table View of Visual Preview means that the attribute is present in the dataset, but does not have a value for that feature.
